  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid for Humanitarian Assistance in Afghanistan and Neighboring Countries</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While the political and conflict developments have dominated Afghanistan&apos;s narrative in recent months, COVID-19 remains a significant challenge for Afghanistan&apos;s population and fragile medical system, that is currently on the brink of collapse.  IOM is already engaged in responding to the immediate humanitarian needs of populations affected or displaced by conflict or natural disasters, internally displaced persons (IDPs) and Afghan returnees, host communities, people with special needs and other vulnerable groups, however needs are quite high and gaps in addressing needs are evident. Through the proposed activities, IOM is building on the existing response to address gaps and novel needs through the provision of emergency shelter and non-food item procurement and distribution, as well as emergency health support to mobile and otherwise vulnerable Afghan populations.</narrative>
  </description>
